# Minty — environment variable reference
#
# None of these are required to run `npm run crm`. They're used by the
# optional data-source importers and the AI backend.
#
# Copy to .env (or set inline on the command line) and pass to node via
# `node --env-file=.env crm/server.js` if you want auto-loading.
#
# NEVER commit a real .env — it's already in .gitignore.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LinkedIn importer — `npm run linkedin`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Path to the extracted LinkedIn data export (from LinkedIn →
# Settings → Data Privacy → Get a copy of your data).
# LINKEDIN_EXPORT_DIR=/path/to/linkedin-export

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Telegram importer — `npm run telegram`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Path to result.json from Telegram Desktop → Settings → Advanced →
# Export Telegram Data → Personal chats + Contacts (format: JSON).
# TELEGRAM_EXPORT_FILE=/path/to/result.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Email (IMAP) importer — `npm run email`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Requires: npm install imap mailparser
# Gmail: create an App Password at myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# EMAIL_HOST=imap.gmail.com
# EMAIL_USER=you@gmail.com
# EMAIL_PASS=your_app_password_here
# EMAIL_PORT=993
# EMAIL_TLS=true

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google OAuth — used by the in-app Gmail + Google Contacts connector
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Setup: console.cloud.google.com → New project → Enable Gmail API
#   → Credentials → Create OAuth 2.0 Client ID → Application type: Desktop app
#   → Authorized redirect URIs: http://localhost:3456/oauth/callback
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
# GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Microsoft OAuth — for Outlook/Hotmail/Microsoft 365 (device flow)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Setup: portal.azure.com → Azure Active Directory → App registrations →
#   New registration → "Accounts in any organizational directory and personal
#   Microsoft accounts" → Certificates & secrets → New client secret
# MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=
# MICROSOFT_CLIENT_SECRET=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Contacts importer (CSV path) — `npm run google-contacts`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Path to CSV exported from contacts.google.com (Google CSV format).
# GOOGLE_CONTACTS_CSV=/path/to/contacts.csv

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SMS importer — `npm run sms`
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# XML export from the SMS Backup & Restore Android app.
# SMS_EXPORT_FILE=/path/to/sms-20240101010101.xml

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Apollo enrichment (OPTIONAL — only importer that hits external APIs)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# APOLLO_API_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AI backend — drives insights, reconnect drafts, network query ranking
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# "claude"  — uses the local Claude Code CLI (claude --print). Default.
# "ollama"  — uses a local Ollama model (no internet, no API key).
AI_BACKEND=claude

# Ollama settings (only used if AI_BACKEND=ollama)
OLLAMA_HOST=http://localhost:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5:7b
